==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propionic
<hw>Pro`pi*on"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pro</ets>to- + Gr. <grk>pi`wn</grk> fat.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, derived from, or designating, an
organic acid which is produced in the distillation of wood, in the
fermentation of various organic substances, as glycerin, calcium
lactate, etc., and is obtained as a colorless liquid having a sharp,
pungent odor. Propionic acid is so called because it is the
<xex>first</xex> or lowest member of the <xex>fatty acid</xex> series
whose salts have a fatty feel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propionyl</ent>⟦br⟧
